In 2011, Moore’s relationship with the former Punk’d star had been plagued by reports that the latter had cheated on his wife with multiple women, and while that was initially believed to be nothing more but a rumor, her decision to end their marriage shortly after was all the confirmation fans needed to know that the allegations were factual after all.

item.title: Which is worse jail or prison?
item.author: youremail@domain.com (Some Person)
item.description: Because prisons are designed for long-term incarceration, they are better developed for the living needs of their populations. Jails, on the other hand, tend to have more transient populations and less well-developed facilities.Click to see full answer. Also, is jail the same thing as prison?Jail and prison are often used interchangeably as places of confinement. If you want to be specific jail can be used to describe a place for those awaiting trial or held for minor crimes, whereas prison describes a place for convicted criminals of serious crimes.
